gomodel:SYNGO_999  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper examines the localization of alphaN-Catenin and Beta-Catenin using pre-embedding immunogold labeling for electron micropscopy. Catenins are cytoplasmatic proteins that bind the Cadherin family of transmembrane proteins.\n\nFigure 3: localization in the adult cerebellar nucleus. 3D: Immunogold staining for beta-catenin, showing clusters of beta-catenin localized at the synaptic junctions nearby both the pre- the postsynaptic plasma membranes. The clusters appear to be located at the rim of transmitter release zones and are partially associated\nwith synaptic vesicle clusters.\n\nFigure 4D: analysis at the cerebral cortex: in axo-spinous synapses (Fig. 4D), the immunolabeling was bordering the release sites and associated with vesicle culsters.\n\nThe above findings suggest both a pre- and postsynaptic localization for beta-Catenin, with a large portion of the signal localized at the rims of the postsynaptic membrane.\n\n*Antibody: 'To detect beta-catenin, we used mouse mAb 5H10 or rabbit polyclonal antibodies (Shibamoto et al., 1995).'. Experimental description: 'Animals: ICR mice and newly hatched chickens were used'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_999" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

